citation_mappings.claim_text: Here’s a list of live interpreter translation services with available pricing structures you can use to estimate a 2-day cost. I’ve focused on services with published rates or typical billing models: 1) Jeenie – On-Demand Live Interpreters Pricing: Pay-as-you-go starting at ≈ $1.99/min for common languages; higher for rare languages (up to ~$4.99/min) and ASL. Video & audio cost the same. Plans reduce per-minute rates with subscriptions ($49/mo, $149/mo, etc.). Jeenie

sources.title: Plans & Pricing | Jeenie
sources.snippet: Get started at $1.99/min. Find a plan that fits your needs. No commitment. No minimums.

citation_mappings.claim_text: 2-Day Pricing Estimate: Low usage (1 hr/day): ~120 min × $1.99 = ~$240 Medium usage (4 hrs/day): ~480 min × $1.29–$1.99 = ~$620–$955 High usage (8 hrs/day): ~960 min × $0.89–$1.99 = ~$855–$1,910 (Depends on plan and language tier.) Jeenie

sources.title: Pay Per Minute Interpreter | LanguageLine Solutions
sources.snippet: Pay Per Minute Interpreter services. No monthly minimums, just pay for the minutes you use. 24/7 access to phone and video interpreting.

citation_mappings.claim_text: 2) LanguageLine Solutions – Pay-Per-Minute Pricing: ~$3.95/min for audio; ~$4.95/min for video interpreting on demand. 24/7 access, no monthly minimums. LanguageLine Solutions

sources.title: Pay Per Minute Interpreter | LanguageLine Solutions
sources.snippet: Pay Per Minute Interpreter services. No monthly minimums, just pay for the minutes you use. 24/7 access to phone and video interpreting.

citation_mappings.claim_text: 2-Day Estimate: 2 hrs/day: 240 min × ~$3.95 = ~$950 (audio) 4 hrs/day: 480 min × ~$4.95 = ~$2,376 (video) 8 hrs/day: 960 min × ~$4.95 = ~$4,752 (video) LanguageLine Solutions
3) Day Interpreting – Pay As You Go Pricing model: Pay-per-minute/prepaid credits; typical prices around $1.25–$1.75/min for many languages (Spanish ~$1.25/min, others ~ $1.75/min). Day Interpreting
2-Day Estimate: 2 hrs/day: 240 min × ~$1.25 = ~$300 4 hrs/day: 480 min × ~$1.75 = ~$840 8 hrs/day: 960 min × ~$1.75 = ~$1,680 Day Interpreting
4) Kings of Translation – Remote On-Demand Pricing: ~$1.29/min for remote phone or secure video interpreting (5-min minimum). On-site interpreters about $80/hr (2-hr min). Kings of Translation

2-Day Estimate (remote): 2 hrs/day: 240 min × $1.29 = ~$310 4 hrs/day: 480 min × $1.29 = ~$620 8 hrs/day: 960 min × $1.29 = ~$1,240 2-Day Estimate (on-site): 16 hrs × $80 = ~$1,280 (minimums apply) Kings of Translation
5) Languagers – On-Demand Interpreting (Pricing on request) Pricing: Professional on-demand phone/video interpreters; exact rates require contacting for a quote. languagers.com

citation_mappings.claim_text: 2-Day Estimate: Depends on language and usage — contact for rates. Notes/Considerations Most interpreter services bill per minute or per hour; 2-day pricing is proportional to usage. Some platforms offer subscriptions that lower per-minute cost if you expect heavy use (e.g., Jeenie). Jeenie
On-site interpreting (in person) will be more expensive due to travel, scheduling, and often multi-hour minimums. Kings of Translation
